:What is "best" is a mater of opinion. I think [[Template:Sisterlinks]] is probably better than [[Template:Associated Wikimedia]] because it doesn't use as much screen space and compliments rather than draw attention away from what a page is about. --<span style="font: bold 10pt 'courier new', comic, sans, ms;">[[User:Darklama|<font color="midnightblue">dark</font>]][[User_talk:Darklama|<font color="green">lama</font>]]</span> 16:43, 19 July 2011 (UTC)
::Yes, the information directly relating to the Wikibooks category is probably the main reason to visit the page so the smaller template is preferable. [[User:Recent Runes|Recent Runes]] ([[User talk:Recent Runes|discuss]] • [[Special:Contributions/Recent Runes|contribs]]) 18:36, 19 July 2011 (UTC)
::The [[Template:Sisterlinks]] template is similar to the [[w:Template:Sister project links]] from Wikipedia. The [[Template:Associated Wikimedia]] template is more powerful for manual control of interWiki links. --[[User:Averaver|Averaver]] ([[User talk:Averaver|discuss]] • [[Special:Contributions/Averaver|contribs]]) 07:45, 20 July 2011 (UTC)

