;Problem 1: Drago deposits 100 into an account at the beginning of each 2-year period for 40 years. The account credits interest at an interest rate of i.
The accumulated amount in the account at the end of the 40 years is 3 times the accumulated amount in the account at the end of 20 years.
Calculate i. {{hidden|Solution| <math>{s}_{\overline{20|}}= 3 {s}_{\overline{10|}}</math> <math> \frac{((1+i)^{20}-1)}{i}=3 \frac{((1+i)^{10}-1)}{i}</math> <math> (1+i)^{20} - 3(1+i)^{10} + 2 = 0 </math> <math> ((1+i)^{10} - 1)((1+i)^{10}-2) = 0 </math> <math>(1+i)^{10}=2</math> <math>(1+i)= 1.07177</math> <math>i_{annual} =.035 </math> }}
